NOTICE — clean-room methodology audit retired the source documentation
(scoped to the current `master` branch only)

The implementation on the current `master` branch was derived from a
trace-document writeup that has been retired by the OxideAV docs audit
dated 2026-05-06. The audit found that the writeup's authoring
methodology did not satisfy clean-room separation (FFmpeg source files
cited as the writeup's basis, not merely as the trace-instrumentation
host). The audit document, including the codec-by-codec verdict, lives
at:

    https://github.com/OxideAV/docs/blob/master/AUDIT-2026-05-06.md

Retired trace document(s) for this codec:
  * video/utvideo/utvideo-trace-reverse-engineering.md

Retirement commit:
    https://github.com/OxideAV/docs/commit/669bc9f
    (docs: retire 8 second-wave trace-RE writeups)

A clean-room rebuild against a strict-isolation workspace
(Specifier / Extractor / Implementer / Auditor roles, with explicit
allow-list and forbidden-input list per role; FFmpeg source excluded
under any path) is on the rebuild backlog, modelled on
docs/video/msmpeg4/ and docs/video/magicyuv/.

Plan: once the clean-room rounds complete and a fresh implementation
derived solely from the new spec is ready, the current `master` branch
will be renamed to `old/master` for archival and a freshly-orphaned
`master` will ship the replacement implementation. The MIT licence
below applies cleanly to that replacement; for any artifact in the
current branch, the contestation status should be assessed against
the audit document.

